==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rosewood
<hw>Rose"wood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A valuable cabinet
wood of a dark red color, streaked and variegated with black, obtained
from several tropical leguminous trees of the genera
<gen>Dalbergia</gen> and <gen>Machaerium</gen>. The finest kind is from
Brazil, and is said to be from the <spn>Dalbergia nigra</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>African rosewood</b></col>, <cd>the wood of the
leguminous tree <spn>Pterocarpus erinaceus</spn>.</cd> --
<col><b>Jamaica rosewood</b></col>, <cd>the wood of two West Indian
trees (<spn>Amyris balsamifera</spn>, and <spn>Linocieria
ligustrina</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>New South Wales rosewood</b></col>,
<cd>the wood of <spn>Trichilia glandulosa</spn>, a tree related to the
margosa.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roseworm</ent>⟦br⟧
